      "question": "An architect is designing a rectangular garden for a community center. The length of the garden is $3 \\text{ m}$ more than twice its breadth. The area of the garden is $119 \\text{ m}^2$. Let the breadth of the garden be $x$ meters. Based on this information, answer the following questions to determine the dimensions of the garden.",
      "type": "case_study",
      "marks": 4,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "i",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "Which of the following quadratic equations represents the given situation?",
          "answer": "(B)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $2x^2 + 3x - 119 = 0$",
            "(B) $2x^2 + 3x - 119 = 0$",
            "(C) $2x^2 - 3x - 119 = 0$",
            "(D) $x^2 + 3x - 238 = 0$"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "ii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the roots of the quadratic equation $2x^2 + 3x - 119 = 0$ using the factorisation method.",
          "answer": "$x = 7, x = -8.5$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Identify the quadratic equation as $2x^2 + 3x - 119 = 0$.",
              "Find two numbers whose product is $2 \\times (-119) = -238$ and sum is $3$. These are $17$ and $-14$.",
              "Rewrite the middle term: $2x^2 - 14x + 17x - 119 = 0$.",
              "Factor by grouping: $2x(x - 7) + 17(x - 7) = 0$.",
              "Solve for $x$: $(2x + 17)(x - 7) = 0$, so $x = 7$ or $x = -17/2 = -8.5$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$2x^2 + 3x - 119 = 0 \\\\ 2x^2 - 14x + 17x - 119 = 0 \\\\ 2x(x - 7) + 17(x - 7) = 0 \\\\ (2x + 17)(x - 7) = 0 \\\\ x = 7, x = -8.5$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "What is the breadth of the garden? Justify your answer.",
          "answer": "$7 \\text{ m}$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "The breadth $x$ must be a positive value because it represents a physical dimension.",
              "Since $x = 7$ and $x = -8.5$ are the roots, we reject the negative root.",
              "Therefore, the breadth is $7 \\text{ m}$."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iv",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the length of the garden.",
          "answer": "$17 \\text{ m}$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "The length is given as $2x + 3$.",
              "Substitute $x = 7$: $2(7) + 3 = 14 + 3 = 17$.",
              "The length of the garden is $17 \\text{ m}$."
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
